(433, 433, '2022-10-20 01:30:45', '2022-10-20 01:30:45', 'TvBtZbCMreE', 'ZepLabs: Quartz: New HomeMade CNC (Part 2)', 'The Quartz! As we presented it and started making it on the last video. It\'s now alive! Well, sort of...\nSee you on the next video,when we\'ll finally talk software I hope..\n\nHere\'s once again the sketchup file, with actual dimensions, in case you want one for yourself:\nhttps://www.dropbox.com/s/9642u4o5kv2j94q/quartz%203035.skp?dl=0\n\nList on the materials:\n(I am also including some links on most of the stuff you are gonna need. Buying through those get\'s me a commission and probably a buck or two. Of course I\'m not expecting of you shopping all your stuff here, but in case you dont have a place in mind, you can find yourself some pretty good deals here actually!)\n- About a quarter sheet of plywood (25 mm thick marine plywood , okoume)\n\n-3 stepper motors (NEMA 17) :\n https://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2FCNC-1-8-Degree-NEMA17-1-7A-40mm-2-Phase-4Lead-Stepper-Motor-For-3D-Printer-New%2F192252132344%3Fhash%3Ditem2cc31ebbf8%3Ag%3AuTsAAOSw5h5ZbtpZ\n\n-A way to mount those!\n  https://www.ebay.com/itm/1PC-Mounting-Bracket-for-Nema-17-Stepper-Motor-3D-Printer-2020-Profiles-42mm/142647082545?hash=item21366dbe31:m:mSwVIzacXIw9yMk0cJ05ETg\n(L bracket)\nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2FBlack-L-Shape-Alloy-Steel-Mounting-Bracket-For-42mm-NEMA17-Stepper-Motor%2F192747371973%3Fepid%3D1363197892%26hash%3Ditem2ce0a37dc5%3Am%3AmxDIiv6ZgfKU3zuQdmILvAQ%3Ark%3A5%3Apf%3A0\n\n-About 2.5 meters of driving belt (10mm wide)\n https://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F1-2-5-10-50-meters-GT2-Timing-Belt-open-6mm-10mm-width-FOR-3D-Printer-Reprap%2F122843727520%3Fhash%3Ditem1c9a0e86a0%3Am%3AmbyBph3JBLg0iAfYjJdL13w\n\n-According pulleys (5mm inner diameter)\nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2FGT2-16T-20Teeth-Bore-3mm-5mm-Idle-Idler-Pulley-Bearing-Wheel-Wide-6-10mm%2F113009301824%3Fhash%3Ditem1a4fe11940%3Am%3AmEiw5oqN_iEszplxtuzIR6A%3Ark%3A2%3Apf%3A0\n\n-8x Linear bearings (LM12UU)\nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F10pcs-LM12UU-12mm-Linear-Motion-Ball-Bearing-Bush-Bushing-12x21x30mm-CNC-Parts%2F300635205784%3Fhash%3Ditem45ff413098%3Ag%3AqR4AAMXQBwlRSV9j\n\n-2x longer linear bearings (for Z) \nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F2pcs-LM12LUU-12mm-Long-Linear-Ball-Bearing-Bush-Bushing-12x21x57mm-3D-Printer%2F272486239248%3Fhash%3Ditem3f71720c10%3Ag%3AVB4AAOSwA3dYT7d2\n\n-Electronics\nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F3D-Printer-Kit-RAMPS-1-4-Mega2560-A4988-12864-LCD-Controller-For-Arduino%2F332566622747%3F_trkparms%3Daid%253D555018%2526algo%253DPL.SIM%2526ao%253D2%2526asc%253D52885%2526meid%253D4c70be2b611c4799851a5acf09b3e885%2526pid%253D100011%2526rk%253D1%2526rkt%253D12%2526sd%253D352216305042%2526itm%253D332566622747%26_trksid%3Dp2047675.c100011.m1850\n\n-Z axis screw 98mm lead/ 2mm pitch / 200 mm length)\n https://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F8mm-Acme-threaded-Rod-trapezoidal-Lead-Screw-T8-Nut-For-CNC-3D-printer-Reprap%2F131817911254%3Fhash%3Ditem1eb0f5b3d6%3Am%3AmWhx1IC5cpKEuMZYIUNDw8Q\n\n-Stepper to thread coupling (5mm to 8mm) \nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2F5-8mm-8-8mm-Aluminum-Shaft-Coupling-Rigid-Coupler-Motor-Connector-For-3D-Printer%2F263933550003%3Fhash%3Ditem3d73aa5db3%3Am%3AmouvclZOQm__YIZiwhXSnjQ\n\n-Vertical flange pillow block\n https://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2FKFL08-8mm-Mounted-Block-Cast-Housing-Self-aligning-Pillow-Bearing-LW%2F182050772715%3Fepid%3D2255374757%26hash%3Ditem2a631256eb%3Ag%3AxMEAAOSwu1VW4j6W\n\n-anti-backlash nut \nhttps://rover.ebay.com/rover/1/711-53200-19255-0/1?icep_id=114&ipn=icep&toolid=20004&campid=5338242550&mpre=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ebay.com%2Fitm%2FT8-8mm-Anti-backlash-Spring-Loaded-Nut-For-3D-Printer-Trapezoidal-Rod-Lead-Screw-%2F323427177279%3Foid%3D322300380923\n\nUntil next time,\nthanks for watching!\nAnd if you like what you see, fell free to subscribe.\nMore coming up!\n\nAnd if you like it too much and wanna help making it even better??\nOk, here is my patreon page!\nhttps://www.patreon.com/ZepLabs\n\nMusic:\nBlues Shuffle in A One Take Improv Exercise by Stevie\'s Amp Shack', '00:00:00', 'TvBtZbCMreE', 'video/youtube', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TvBtZbCMreE/mqdefault.jpg', '(min-width: 400px;)', 'image/jpeg', 'UCjoAeGYdt4nFPu_SHoT3P7A', '2019-03-22 03:46:11'),
(434, 434, '2022-10-20 01:30:45', '2022-10-20 01:30:45', 'TSfRXPSDhsA', 'X-WOOD - 1# MINI CNC FÁCIL E BARATA - FAÇA VOCÊ MESMO. DIY CNC - VIDEO 1', 'Finalmente comecei a fazer a minha CNC.\nDepois de muita pesquisa, comprei os materiais  e coloquei a mão na massa.\nEsse é o vídeo 1 de uma série de vídeos sobre a CNC.\nNão esqueça o joinha e se inscreva no canal para não perder os próximos vídeos.\nValeu.\n\nArquivo:\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/0B3HftVqWfJhcTGFWalVOcVpPclU/view?usp=sharing', '00:00:00', 'TSfRXPSDhsA', 'video/youtube', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/TSfRXPSDhsA/mqdefault.jpg', '(min-width: 400px;)', 'image/jpeg', 'UCjoAeGYdt4nFPu_SHoT3P7A', '2019-03-23 03:40:09'),
(435, 435, '2022-10-20 01:30:45', '2022-10-20 01:30:45', 'I7woln6urVY', 'DIY Dremel CNC #1 design and parts (Arduino, aluminium profiles, 3D printed parts)', 'DIY CNC machine is a very popular project on the internet, a lot of people made different versions but I want to show you how I made my own CNC machine with a Dremel as a spindle. Personally, I think that CNC machine is kind of an upgrade of a 3D printer, you can create stronger parts made out of wood or metal but it also has some limitations (that\'s a topic for another video). \n\nDremel CNC parts list: https://bit.ly/2Hmlbcw\nFacebook group: https://bit.ly/2JOdv5s\nInstructables: https://bit.ly/2wvViAF\nThingiverse: https://bit.ly/2HKHzfO\n\nSupport my projects on Patreon → https://www.patreon.com/nikodembartnik\nOr through PayPal: https://www.paypal.me/nikodembartnik\n\nWhat we will need, amount in ():\n-Dremel tool\n-Aluminum Profiles 20x20x600mm (5): https://goo.gl/DtTTiD\n-12mm rod (about 2 meters): https://goo.gl/QKg2bN\n-500mm long trapezoidal lead screw 8mm (2): https://goo.gl/paVrpV\n-300mm long trapezoidal lead screw 8mm (2): https://goo.gl/paVrpV\n-12mm linear bearing (12): https://goo.gl/uA5ho4\n-5 to 8mm coupler (5): https://goo.gl/YPHCY6\n-T nut (50): https://goo.gl/BNi4zf\n-Screws: https://goo.gl/2USpv5\n\n-Arduino+CNC shield+stepper drivers: https://goo.gl/516Bue\n-Power supply: https://goo.gl/NfkWaT\n-Stepper motors (4): https://goo.gl/7juH9o\n\nIn the first part of my DIY Dremel CNC, I will show you how my design looks like (if you have any idea on how to make it better or you see some problems please let me know :)) I will also show you all the parts that I will use in next parts of this short series. In the next two or three videos, we will assemble this machine and hopefully mill some stuff.\n\nSubscribe and follow to stay tuned:\nYouTube: https://goo.gl/x6Y32E\nInstagram: https://goo.gl/JLFLtf', '00:00:00', 'I7woln6urVY', 'video/youtube', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/I7woln6urVY/mqdefault.jpg', '(min-width: 400px;)', 'image/jpeg', 'UCjoAeGYdt4nFPu_SHoT3P7A', '2019-03-23 09:22:43'),
(436, 436, '2022-10-20 01:30:45', '2022-10-20 01:30:45', 'hB4Cvbtu-lA', 'Banggood 3018 Mini Cnc Router Kit Build, Test & Review', 'In this video I built a mini cnc kit and tested it with wood, acrylic, aluminium and fr4 pcb material.\n\nBanggood 3018 Mini Cnc Router Kit     https://www.banggood.com/custlink/K3mKbMkHyf       \n\nER11 collet holder     https://www.banggood.com/custlink/DDK32OntlI\n(To install the collet holder, heat it up and tap it onto the spindle motor shaft)\n\nEnd Mills 1 - 3mm    https://www.banggood.com/custlink/KG33MjQ54p\n\n22mm surface planing bit     https://www.banggood.com/custlink/vGvE8OZoK2\n(Use with an ER11  6mm collet for spoil board surfacing)\n\nhttp://www.techydiy.org/banggood-3018-3-axis-mini-cnc-router-build-test-review/\nhttps://github.com/trasz/grblControl      \nhttp://easel.inventables.com/\nhttp://flatcam.org/\n\nOther mini cnc videos:\nEleksmill    https://youtu.be/MG5BQI3h6Ek   (Best for pcb milling)\n3018-MX3    https://youtu.be/N2UOCccnewE   (For Mach3 software)', '00:00:00', 'hB4Cvbtu-lA', 'video/youtube', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/hB4Cvbtu-lA/mqdefault.jpg', '(min-width: 400px;)', 'image/jpeg', 'UCjoAeGYdt4nFPu_SHoT3P7A', '2019-03-23 10:59:41'),
