(671, 671, '2022-10-20 11:23:08', '2022-10-20 11:23:08', 'nfoWN7jXE4Y', 'Upgrade Marlin 2.0 firmware on ANET A8 v1.0 Board', 'How to upgrade Marlin 2.0 Firmware on an ANET A8 v1.0 board without running out of memory space.\n\nWith Marlin 2.0.7.2+ you will need to use VSCODE with PlatformIO and Auto Build Marlin plugins installed to compile Marlin.\n\nANET A8 Board Definitions\nhttps://github.com/SkyNet3D/anet-board\n\nReduce the size of Marlin Article\nhttps://thborges.github.io/blog/marlin/2019/01/07/reducing-marlin-binary-size.html\n\nMy Configuration.h, Configuration_adv.h, and _statusscreen.h files I use to configure my ANET A8 v1.0 board.\nhttps://drive.google.com/file/d/18pQaQh8n0G9K7euj6g-O5rptCWeBY1X6/view?usp=sharing', '00:00:00', 'nfoWN7jXE4Y', 'video/youtube', 'https://i.ytimg.com/vi/nfoWN7jXE4Y/mqdefault.jpg', '(min-width: 400px;)', 'image/jpeg', 'UCxytNNPtemfYjvq2TQJC2Fw', '2021-08-26 02:40:30'),
