(673, 673, '2022-10-20 11:23:08', '2022-10-20 11:23:08', '38PkynA1uGI', 'Anet A8 (Plus) Marlin 2.0 Installation Upgrade', 'Anet A8 (Plus) Marlin 2.0 Installation Upgrade\n\nIn this video, I show you how to install Marlin 2.0 firmware on the Anet A8 or the Anet A8 plus using Visual Studio Code and Platform IO as well as the new Auto Build Marlin plugin, which makes this a much easier process. Also you will see some troubleshooting tips.\n\nRead the blogpost here, if you prefer a written version: https://www.crosslink.io/2020/03/19/anet-a8-plus-marlin-2-0-installation-upgrade/\n\n*** Get the Anet A8 here\n🛒 Amazon: https://geni.us/aneta8\n\n*** Videos referred to in this video:\nShould you upgrade to Marlin 2.0?\nhttps://youtu.be/rjRmBbuN6iA\n\nHow to install a bootloader on the Anet A8 using an Arduino UNO\nhttps://youtu.be/RQIizXtf9oo\n\nHow to install a bootloader on the Anet A8 using a programmer device\nhttps://youtu.be/wRODgnAqp1A\n\nHow to use Mesh Bed Leveling on the Anet A8\nhttps://youtu.be/ADdzKyS-T3w\n\nMy blogpost about memory usage of Marlin on 8Bit boards and how to fix size issues\nhttps://www.crosslink.io/marlin-2-0-memory-usage-by-feature/\n\n*** Programmer devices for flashing a bootloader\nUSBAsp\nhttps://geni.us/usbasp\n\nUSBTinyISP\nhttps://geni.us/usbtinyisp\n\n10 pin to 6 pin adapter\nhttps://geni.us/10to6pinadapter\n\n*** Software links\nMarlin firmware\nhttps://github.com/MarlinFirmware/Marlin\n\nMarlin Default Configuration Files\nhttps://github.com/MarlinFirmware/Configurations\n\nVisual Studio Code\nhttps://visualstudio.microsoft.com/\n\nTHE PRINTERS I USE: https://kit.co/danielcrosslink/the-3d-printers-i-use\nMY MERCH: https://crosslink.io/shop\n\nBECOME A PATRON: https://www.patreon.com/crosslink\nCHAT ON DISCORD: https://discord.gg/ne3J4Rf\n\nBUSINESS INQUIRIES ONLY (OR IF YOU WANT TO SEND SOMETHING) - DANIEL@CROSSLINK.IO\n\nFOLLOW ME:\nINSTAGRAM - https://instagram.com/danielcrosslink\nTWITTER - https://twitter.com/danielcrosslink\nFAC