(1968, 1968, '2022-11-09 12:18:29', '2022-11-09 12:18:29', 'GlkbeIv6kBM', 'Tutorial - Beautiful Water Feature Fluid Simulation in Blender and Mantaflow', 'Support me on Patreon to receive the fountain starter file, if you want to skip straight to the fun part: https://www.patreon.com/posts/36919800\n\nI really enjoyed playing with the new Mantaflow fluid simulation solver in Blender 2.82. As someone who has been using Blender for fluid simulation for years now, I have wished for this update for a long time. Let\'s hope they soon update Bullet Physics in the rigid body physics, to support GPU acceleration, or at least multithreading… We can only dream.\n\nMy second Blender 2.8 tutorial, again in blender 2.82. This should apply to any version of Blender from 2.82 onwards, but from my understanding, this new fluid simulation tool is only available from 2.82, so you won\'t be able to do it with earlier versions. \n\nNew material links! For a while, the materials couldn’t be downloaded because Syncretic 3D took down the mentioned videos. But, he has very kindly allowed me to share the materials with you. Download them at the updated google drive links below.\n\nLinks:\nReference Image - https://imgur.com/a/XtTwu9q\nHDR Map  - http://www.hdrlabs.com/sibl/archive.html\nConcrete material, new link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/1wjlOm87irl2LdHduZkyBz9uJ2P-TZzFS/view?usp=sharing\nGranite material, new link - https://drive.google.com/file/d/17qkHVHro14E8eFclf_kcp3OXE3yp0PQo/view?usp=sharing\n\nOld broken links for materials:\nGranite Material - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WkqFS78yS8M\nCement Material - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J-a2HYlu6nM\n\nTime codes:\n00:00 - Hello\n01:25 - Modelling\n21:15 - Materials\n28:10 - Image based HDI hack\n32:25 - New fluid simulation solver!\n45:03 - Easy camera movement trick\n55:55 - Compositing\n\n- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - \n\nPatreon    